metadata.name: Divide by Circle #503
metadata.description:
An experiment with subdivision, cubes, and a circle.
There are many parameters and special features.
Click to randomize divisions with the same settings.
Unminted editions over 100 will be burnt after 24 hours.

By Frank Force @KilledByAPixel
Made with JavaScript and Three.js

Live Mode Controls
1 - Save 2048x2048 png with SSAA
2 - Toggle noise
3 - Toggle animation
4 - Randomize every 10 seconds

metadata.name: Subdivision: forms and feelings #36
Brosser #199
metadata.description:
Exploring generative brush strokes to simulate real life paintings. 

- A selection of 19 different palettes
- 4 different drawing styles
- Randomized "color swap" between the primary and secondary colors in each palette

Several other factors determine the output of a piece, including angles, depth, brush length, and brush weight, among others.

metadata.name: Lookouts #83
metadata.description:
Lookouts is a generative illustration done 100% in code using p5js. Inspired by my love for travel and minimalist design, this collection is built based on custom shapes filled with solid colors & limited texture.

The accompanying fxtext article (in ‘Mentions’ below) shares more details about the inspiration and development process of this project.

Lookouts renders as a fixed resolution output (2000 x 1666px). Controls (in live view): 
Press [4] to render at 4000 x 3333px
Press [8] to render at 8000 x 6666px
Press [s] to save the current view (default or higher resolution image)

metadata.name: (recombination/perspectives)-I: Horizons #9
metadata.description:
🌊 🌞 🌈 🌅


    ( r e c o m b i n a t i o n  /  p e r s p e c t i v e s ) 


                     I :   H o r i z o n s


                            ✨ 🧬 🧡 ⏲







-----
* What/How *

2 560 000 particles are subjected to a succession of 64 energy bursts which scatters the points through space. 
The algorithm then stores 3 configurations of points, forming an entangled coherent system.
After few seconds multiple observation modalities are then selected sequentially to allow for dynamic and contemplative visualization.

-----
* Mint preview *

Minter will get a 2160x2160 PNG bitmap and an infinite randomly deterministic animation.

-----
* Technics *

This experience is designed to be executed on a recent GPU (>2016) and displayed on 16/9 screens from FHD to 8K+ (1920x1080 → 7680x4320) at 60FPS for infinite duration.

- JavaScript / ThreeJS / WebGL / GLSL
- Unique generative, random and determinist animation (animation is seeded by the fxhash mint hash)
- Infinite animation
- Animation sequences duration between 6 and 60 seconds.

-----
* Controls *

Keyboard "Space" : take a PNG capture of the current view frame (same ratio as window, max 1920x1080)

Keyboard "X" : skip current animation sequence / next sequence

-----
* URL modifiers *

"&fastdemo=on"
Forces animation sequences to last 10 seconds instead of random durations.

"&slow=on"
Forces animation sequences to last 1 minute instead of random durations.

"&static=on"
Disables animation automatic start. Press "X" to start animations.


-----
@HAL09999 – January 25th, 2023
